@node MENUS "The menus"

@{b}@{u}NoStAlGiA@{uu}@{ub} : - @{b}About@{ub} : display the about box.
            - @{b}Quit@{ub}  : Close Nostalgia!

@{b}@{u}List@{uu}@{ub} : - @{b}xxx games@{ub} : Lists only the games of the xxx console.
       - @{b}All games@{ub} : List all the available games.

@endnode
@node KEYCUT "Keyboard shortcuts"

@{b}ESC@{ub} : Close a window or quit Nostalgia!

@{b}SPACE@{ub} : Display/Close the full sized display of the preview.

@{b}ENTER@{ub} : Run the selected emulation.

@endnode

@node REQUIREMENTS "Requirements"

@{b}@{u}Minimal requirements :@{uu}@{ub}

    - an Amiga or a Pegasos
    - AmigaOS 3.x, MorphOS
    - at least a 68020
    - High resolution screen (at least 800*600)
    - some Fast RAM (4Mb should be enough...)

@{b}@{u}Recommended :@{uu}@{ub}

    - 040 or 060 and PPC (not needed by Nostalgia! but by the emulators...)
    - a GFX board (any WB emulation)
    - 8Mb Fast RAM
    - Some roms :o)
    - these emulators : AmiGenerator, DarcNes, Handy, GBE, WarpSNES, WarpNeoMAME, NeoMAME, TrueReality, WarpTGEmu, FPSE, SNES9x, Snes9x-MOS, TGemu-MOS, SMSPlus-MOS, GenesisPlus-MOS.

@endnode

@node BUGS "Known bugs"

I spent a lot of time for the debugging so I hope there is no more bugs.
There is actually no known bugs but if you encountered one, please @{"contact" link CONTACT} me.

@endnode

@node INSTALLATION "Installation"

@{b}@{u}For Nostalgia! itself :@{uu}@{ub}

    - Simply double click on the installation script.
    - To uninstall Nostalgia!, simply delete the Nostalgia directory, all the
      preferences files are kept within.


@{b}@{u}For the emulators :@{uu}@{ub}

@{b}!!! we assume that "Nostalgia:" is the complete path of the installed Nostalgia! system !!! @{ub}

    - @{b}AmiGenerator@{ub} : get the archive, uncompress it and copy the AmiGeneratorT.exe executable file
                     in "Nostalgia:bin/.
                     Rename AmiGeneratorT.exe to amigenerator.
                     The name @{b}MUST@{ub} be "amigenerator".

    - @{b}DarcNes@{ub} : idem but also, copy the file "COLECO.ROM" in the same
              directory as the executable file.
              For CDROM support, you need the file "syscard3.pce" and copy it to Nostalgia:bin/
                The name @{b}MUST@{ub} be "darcnes".

    - @{b}GBE@{ub} : idem.
            The name @{b}MUST@{ub} be "gbe".

    - @{b}Handy@{ub} : idem but also copy the file "lynxboot.img" in the same directory
              as the executable file.
              The name @{b}MUST@{ub} be "handy".

    - @{b}WarpSNES@{ub} : idem.
                 The name @{b}MUST@{ub} be "warpsnes".

    - @{b}WarpNeoMAME@{ub} : idem but the file "NEOGEO.ZIP" must be copied in
                    Nostalgia:roms/NeoGeo.
                    The name @{b}MUST@{ub} be "warpneomame" and "warpkickstart".

    - @{b}NeoMAME@{ub} : idem than WarpNeoMAME.
                The name @{b}MUST@{ub} be "neomame".

    - @{b}SNES9x@{ub} : idem than WarpSNES.
               The name @{b}MUST@{ub} be "snes9x".

    - @{b}TrueReality@{ub} : idem.
                    The name @{b}MUST@{ub} be "truereality".

    - @{b}FPSE@{ub} : idem but the file "SCPH1001.bin" must be copied in Nostalgia:bin/
             The name @{b}MUST@{ub} be "fpse".

    - @{b}WarpTGEmu@{ub} : idem than DarcNes.
                  The name @{b}MUST@{ub} be "warptgemu".

    - @{b}Snes9x-MOS@{ub} : idem than WarpSNES.
                  The name @{b}MUST@{ub} be "snes9x-mos".

    - @{b}TGemu-MOS@{ub} : idem than WarpTGEmu.
                  The name @{b}MUST@{ub} be "tgemu-mos".

    - @{b}SMSPlus-MOS@{ub} : idem than DarcNes.
                  The name @{b}MUST@{ub} be "smsplus-mos".

    - @{b}GenesisPlus-MOS@{ub} : idem than AmiGenerator.
                  The name @{b}MUST@{ub} be "genesisplus-mos".

@{b}@{u}For the roms :@{uu}@{ub}

    - They must all be copied in their corresponding directories in
      "Nostalgia:roms/".
      @{b}NEVER@{ub} put a rom in the roms/ path otherwise it will never appear, place
      them in their correspondig sub-directory (roms/Nes or roms/ColecoVisio for
      example).

    - The roms @{b}MUST@{ub} have the good extension.
      The actual supported extensions are :

        - .bin, .smd for Megadrive/Genesis roms
        - .col for ColecoVision roms    @{b}<=== VERY IMPORTANT@{ub}
        - .sms for MasterSystem roms
        - .gg for GameGear roms
        - .nes for NES roms
        - .pce for PCEngine roms
        - .gb, .gbc for GameBoy and GameBoyColor roms
        - .lnx for Lynx roms
        - .smc, .swc, .fig, .sfc for SNES roms
        - .zip for NeoGeo roms
        - .n64, v64 for Nintendo64 roms.
        - .exe for Playstation roms.



@endnode

@node TODO "To Do..."

Nostalgia! is quite complete but it can be completed a lot, in fact, my idea is now to transform Nostalgia in a complete centralized system for managing roms and emulation, you will be able to tweak the system and make it suit your need in a level of details you wouldn't imagine :

    - Fully skinnable
    - Based on a complete database system so that you would be able to customize Nostalgia's behaviour for each rom you have (emulator, parameters, etc etc ... customizable for each rom independantly)
    - More interactions with Internet.
    - Resizeable window
    - Cleaner "running from WB" procedure...
    - Customizable ROM list
    - More keyboard shortcuts
    - AmigaOS 4.0/MorphOS version
    - Support for many other emulators such as WES (especially thanks to the database system)


@endnode

@node HISTORY "History"
@{b}@{u}2.3@{uu}@{ub} : - Added support for 2 more MorphOS emulators : SMSPlus-MOS and GenesisPlus-MOS

@{b}@{u}2.2@{uu}@{ub} : - Added support for MorphOS emulators : Snes9x-MOS and TGemu-MOS
      - Corrected few minor bugs in running games with Snes9x.
      - Nostalgia support some MOS emulators but it is NOT a MOS application, currently, it is still an Amiga 68k app so it still runs on Classic Amigas.

@{b}@{u}2.1@{uu}@{ub} : - Recompiled with StormC 4.0/GCC ==> Now ready for native AmigaOS 4.0 and/or MorphOS port.
      - Fixed a crash when running on a CPU witout FPU.
      - Added a realtime update of the preview when listing roms with the keyboard.
      - Fixed crash when changing ChunkyPPC.library preferences in WarpSNES preferences window.
      - Fixed some strange behaviour with some rom launching, now, Nostalgia should behave exactly as what you can achieve with shell directly.
      - Fixed AmiGenerator 0.33+ support, now fully functionnal but only with the "T" version of AmiGenerator.
      - Changed the code to run Nostalgia even if OpenURL.library is not present (in this case, Internet functions are not activated)

@{b}@{u}2.0@{uu}@{ub} : - MAJOR UPDATE !!!
      - Recompiled with StormC 4.0
      - Added support for SNES9x, NeoMAME, FPSE, TrueReality and WarpTGEmu !
      - Added progression gauge for "About box"
      - Added preferences for Nostalgia settings
      - "skin" function
